Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Instance 1: Constructs Involved: Place Order, Validate Order Parameters, include relationship from Place Order to Validate Order Parameters
   Instance 1: Explanation: "Validate Order Parameters" is an inclusion use case included only by "Place Order". It is not associated with any actor, does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is not part of any generalization hierarchy. It represents a sub-step (validating parameters) of placing an order rather than a complete, standalone service observable to any actor. This is functional decomposition of "Place Order" into a procedural sub-step.

   Instance 2: Constructs Involved: Execute Trade, Route to Exchange, include relationship from Execute Trade to Route to Exchange
   Instance 2: Explanation: "Route to Exchange" is an inclusion use case included only by "Execute Trade". It is not associated with any actor, does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is not part of any generalization hierarchy. Routing to an exchange is an internal implementation step of executing a trade, not a complete service yielding an observable result to a user. This is functional decomposition of "Execute Trade".

   Instance 3: Constructs Involved: View Portfolio, Fetch Account Data, include relationship from View Portfolio to Fetch Account Data
